The paper deals with communication systems and their performance analysis, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. The use of random beamforming and multiuser diversity also suggests the Signal Processing (cs.SI) category. The analysis of individual sum rate and scaling laws involves mathematical techniques such as probability theory and extreme value theory, which are relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) categories.
